Description: a terminal where paste is safe by construction
 secure-terminal is a small, line-oriented terminal for pasting commands into,
 and reading text out of, without worrying about invisible characters, bidi
 overrides or escape sequences. Its display is printable ASCII only (everything
 else is neutralized, the way stcat does for logs) and it interprets no escape
 sequences from program output, so a pasted or printed lie cannot redraw or
 reorder what you see. Paste is sanitized to ASCII before it reaches the shell.
 .
 Input forwards printable ASCII plus a tiny allowlist of control keys that the
 pseudo-terminal turns into signals: Ctrl+C (SIGINT), Ctrl+Z (SIGTSTP),
 Ctrl+\\ (SIGQUIT) and Ctrl+D (EOF). It is not a curses host: full-screen TUIs
 (nano, vim, emacs) are out of scope by design, because supporting them means
 parsing exactly the escape sequences this terminal exists to refuse. Built with
 Python and Qt6.
